# Archie Lillingston – Character File

**Project:** Lonesome Trail (Working Title)
**Created:** February 17, 2026
**Author:** Dale Salvador

---

## Overview

Archie Lillingston, also known as **Archibald Lillingston** or *“The Quiet Broker”*, serves as a central quest giver and merchant in Bunco City. Calm, calculating, and observant, he operates a public bar while secretly managing an arms dealing network.

His offers and quests adapt to the player’s moral path, subtly influencing progression without judgment.

---

## Role & Occupation

* **Primary Role:** Bartender (public)
* **Secondary Role:** Arms Dealer (hidden)
* **Narrative Function:**

  * Facilitates all major player quests
  * Maintains influence over city events and economy
  * Acts as a moral-neutral force, reflecting the consequences of player choices

---

## Family Background

* Wealthy, influential in Bunco City’s alcohol industry
* Controls supply and distribution across Bunco and surrounding towns
* Emphasizes strategic control and long-term planning

---

## Personality & Demeanor

* **Traits:** Calm, patient, calculating, observant, adaptive, rarely reactive
* **Demeanor:** Neutral, business-like; avoids emotional displays
* **Philosophy:** Control above all; influence is maintained through peace or violence

---

## Appearance

* Well-dressed, unassuming, always composed
* Bar reflects personality: clean, organized, meticulous

**Typical Clothing:**

* Waistcoat
* Shirt with rolled sleeves
* Sturdy boots
* Minimal accessories

---

## Dialogue Style

* Neutral, measured, business-oriented
* **Examples:**

  * “There’s a man blocking opportunity. I’d appreciate it if that obstacle were removed.”
  * “Your path seems set. I can assist accordingly.”
  * “Whether you choose peace or chaos, Bunco has room for you. Just know I always see the bigger picture.”

---

## Quest Mechanics

### Rider Path (Violent)

* **Quest Name:** Expansion Contract
* **Description:** Player eliminates obstacles to establish a new bar in a rival town
* **Reward:** Weapons, resources, and access to the hidden "Second Shop"
* **Conditions:** Player pursues violence and outlaw status

### Domestic Path (Peaceful)

* **Quest Name:** Bar Assistant
* **Description:** Player manages bar operations, supplies, and builds local relationships
* **Reward:** Safe income, minor story influence, no weapon access
* **Conditions:** Player chooses domestic/love-oriented path

### Second Shop (Unlockable)

* **Description:** Arms dealer network; accessible only on Rider path
* **Location:** Hidden area behind the bar
* **Tone:** Cold, business-like; no morality discussion
* **Inventory:** Weapons, explosives, specialized gear

---

## Relationships

* **Player:** Manipulative facilitator; adapts quests to player choices
* **Girl Character:** Observant; senses influence instinctively
* **Father Rufus Mutz:** Indirect ally; respects authority when beneficial
* **Sheriff George Storen:** Strategic relationship; uses influence or bribes to clear obstacles

---

## Notes

* Reacts only to usefulness, never moral judgment
* Player perception changes with choices, behavior remains constant
* Optional lore hints can appear in bar decor and ledgers, showing empire-building and strategic planning
